  "instructions": [
    "In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the caraway seeds and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the smoked paprika and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the dried navy beans, salt, and pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the water and bring to a boil.",
    "Transfer the saucepan to a preheated tagine or Dutch oven and cover.",
    "Bake at 300°F (150°C) for 45 minutes, or until the beans are tender.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley and serve hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
